340 g Turkey Breast Portions
227 g Fresh Linguine
1 unit Sweet Bell Pepper
28 g Baby Spinach
1 unit Chili Pepper
1 unit Crushed Tomatoes with Garlic and Onion
7 g Parsley
7 g Zesty Garlic Blend
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
7.5 g Chicken Stock Powder
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
¼ tsp Sugar*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450°F.
Wash and dry all produce.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil over high.
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
While pan heats, pat turkey dry with paper towels, then season with Zesty Garlic blend, salt and pepper.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil and turkey. Sear turkey for 2-3 min per side, until golden.
Transfer to prepared baking sheet. Wipe out pan.

Roast turkey in the middle of the oven for 8-12 min, until turkey is cooked through.
When cooked, transfer turkey to a plate to rest for 3-4 min.

While turkey roasts, core, then thinly slice sweet bell pepper.
Roughly chop spinach. (TIP: Place spinach in a bowl, then roughly chop using a pair of kitchen shears or scissors.)
Roughly chop parsley.
Finely chop chili, removing seeds for less heat. (TIP: We suggest using gloves when prepping chilis.)

Reheat the same pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and sweet bell pepper. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 3-4 min, stirring often until tender-crisp.
Add crushed tomatoes, stock powder, 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and half the chili peppers. (Like things spicy? Add more chilli peppers to taste!) Season with salt and pepper. Bring sauce to a simmer.

Reduce heat to medium-low. Cook for 3-5 min, stirrng occasionally until sauce thickens slightly.
While sauce simmers, add linguine to the boiling water. Cook for 2-4 min, stirring occasionally, until tender but still firm to the bite.
Reserve 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) pasta water. Strain linguine, then add directly to sauce.
Add spinach. Toss to coat for 1 min, until spinach wilts.

Thinly slice turkey.
Divide linguine between plates.
Top with turkey.
Sprinkle Parmesan and parsley over top.